      "stem_html": "<p>Lithocholic acid is an A–B cis steroid found in human bile. Draw lithocholic acid showing chair conformations, as in Figure 27.12, and tell whether the hydroxyl group at C3 is axial or equatorial.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBbGdZIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--55c5c7f927b9c5d1a72de5ecfafd281353714b3d/OChem_27_06_006.jpg\" alt=\"The figure shows the wedge-dash structure of lithocholic acid.\">",
